item.title: Resources
item.description: Learning Thomas Wong’s textbook is an introductory book which takes the time to give you the foundations in classical computing before teaching you quantum computing. Q is for Quantum stuff Qiskit is a library for running quantum circuits, and they have a series of tutorials going in depth on how to design them. Pennylane is a framework for quantum machine learning, and they have nicely illustrated explanations of many quantum concepts.
